[[File:Recording_Rod.png|thumb|right|150px|A recording rod]]
'''Recording rods''', also known as '''recording units''', were long, clear cylindrical tubes that recorded and played audio and visual images. The data was stored in chips or storage crystals and the recording material played in two-dimensions on the exterior of the rod. The controls were located on the ends of the rod.

==Characteristics==
Recording rods were devices for personal use that were capable of recording [[Standard hour/Legends|hours]] of audio and video. The recordings could then be played back on standard audio, video, or [[Holoprojector/Legends|holoprojectors]]. Recording rods used [[Datachip/Legends|datachips]] and [[storage crystal]]s to store their data.<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> Some recording rods were cylindrical and clear, capable of storing video and audio. These recordings could then be played back and viewed on the rod's surface. These recording rods were designed to be reusable, but overwriting data on the rod led to the deletion of the stored data.<ref name="RPG-Core">''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Core Rulebook]]''</ref>

Mass-market recording rods offered good-quality recording at reasonable prices. More specialized recording rods were also available, ranging from miniaturized units to professional-grade models that were used in the entertainment and news industries. These models could cost hundreds of [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] apiece, and included equipment such as better recording optics and audio pickups and enhanced storage capacity that could hold up to a thousand hours of data.<ref name="EGWT" />

==History==
Recording rods had multiple uses, ranging from the personal such as sending messages to friends and family, and maintaining personal logs and diaries. They were used by [[Scout/Legends|scouts]] and [[Police officer/Legends|police officers]] during missions and investigations, as well as to record official governmental and corporate meetings. [[Tagge Company/Legends|TaggeCo.]] produced the [[PersonalAssistant-4x recording rod]].<ref name="EGWT" />

